$(tag).text("any text");

$(tag).queue() : gives all the functions that are applied on the selected dag
$(tag).dequeue()
$(tag).clearQueue();

$().animate({property,'value'},time);

callback functions in jQuery

chaining : using multiple effects/actions/methods together on a tag;
example:
$('.animated_div').css('background-color','green').slideUp(5000).css('color','red').slideDown(5000);

.css
3 methods
	.css('css property','value'); // single
	
	.css({'property' :'value',
			'propert' : 'value',
			}); // multiple 

	.css('border-width',function(){
		// no idea
	});

$(tag).html :selected elements ke contents set karta hai
ex: $().html(function(){})	# ek daach use hto 

$().addClass() : adds one or more class names to selected elements

$().removeClass() : removes one or more class names from selected elements

$().toggleClass() : toggles between add and remove class


$().remove(tag);
	removes all the selected elements including data,events,child,etc.
$().detach();
	removes only elements and not data and events
$().empty();


video : 23
$().attr(); and $().prop(); are same

$().removeAttr('attr_to_be_removed','value') : removes the selected property 

$().removeProp(); will remove the entire element
remove is not working properly in jq 3.3.1.min.js


